# NestJS Backend Rules

Read `ai-context/data-model.md` and `ai-context/api-design.md` for full context.

## Module Structure

Each feature module is self-contained:
```
backend/src/<module>/
  ├── <module>.controller.ts
  ├── <module>.service.ts
  ├── <module>.module.ts
  ├── schemas/          # Mongoose schemas
  └── dto/              # Request/response DTOs
```

## Conventions

- Validate all input via DTOs with `class-validator` decorators
- Use Mongoose schemas with `@Schema()` / `@Prop()` decorators
- All endpoints (except auth) require `@UseGuards(JwtAuthGuard)`
- Return consistent response shape: `{ data, message? }`
- Use MongoDB aggregation pipelines for reports (not app-level loops)

## Auth Flow

1. User hits `GET /api/auth/google` → redirect to Google
2. Google callback → validate, upsert user, return JWT
3. All subsequent requests use `Authorization: Bearer <jwt>`

## Error Handling

- Use NestJS built-in exception filters
- Throw `NotFoundException`, `BadRequestException`, etc.
- Never expose internal error details to client
